# HYG Dynamic Fair-Value Model — Technical Specification

**Author:** Internal — Optiver US Credit
**Version:** 0.1
**Scope:** End-to-end specification for a partial-adjustment, regime-switching, fast-to-slow pricing model for HYG using ES1, ZN1, CL1 (hedgeable) and MOVE, VIX (signal-only) as fast factors. The framework generalises to LQD, JNK, IGSB, EMB and other bond ETFs by adjusting the factor set.

---

## 0. Notation and Conventions

| Symbol | Meaning |
|---|---|
| $S_t$ | Log mid of HYG at event-time $t$ |
| $\mathbf{F}_t^H$ | Hedgeable fast-factor vector (log mids) |
| $\mathbf{F}_t^S$ | Signal-only fast-factor vector |
| $\boldsymbol{\beta}_t$ | Time-varying loadings on $\mathbf{F}_t^H$ |
| $\boldsymbol{\gamma}_t$ | Time-varying loadings on $\mathbf{F}_t^S$ |
| $\boldsymbol{\phi}_{k,t}$ | Distributed-lag coefficients on $\Delta\mathbf{F}_{t-k}$ |
| $\alpha_t$ | Drifting intercept (NAV-premium proxy) |
| $V_t$ | Implied fair-value log price |
| $z_t = S_t - V_t$ | Basis |
| $M_t, R_t$ | Mean-reverting and random-walk components of $z_t$ |
| $s_t \in \{N,S\}$ | Latent regime (Normal / Stress) |
| $\delta_{s_t}$ | Pass-through coefficient |
| $\kappa_{s_t}$ | Error-correction speed |
| $\pi_t(j)$ | Filtered regime probability |
| $\tilde{M}_t$ | Conformal z-score on $M_t$ |

All times are stored in nanosecond UTC epoch. All prices are log-prices unless stated. All bar widths and discount factors are stated relative to a 5-second base unit, with conversion rules given where they apply.

