## 10. Trading Rule

### 10.1 Signal triggers

Entry condition (per event):
$$|\tilde{M}_t| > U_\alpha \quad \text{AND} \quad \pi_t(N) > 0.7 \quad \text{AND} \quad \text{current spread on HYG} \leq \text{spread}_{\max}$$

The spread filter prevents trying to trade during liquidity vacuums where the model thinks the basis is wide but execution would consume any expected edge.

Exit conditions (any of):
- $|\tilde{M}_t| < U_\alpha / 2$ — basis has materially closed
- $\pi_t(S) > 0.5$ — regime flip detected
- Position age exceeds 30 minutes — staleness cutoff
- Realised P&L on position exceeds $+ 2 \times$ expected edge — take profit
- Realised P&L on position exceeds $- 1 \times$ expected edge — stop loss
- 12:30 ET on early-close days, 15:50 ET on regular days — flatten before close

### 10.2 Sizing

Target position size in HYG units:
$$w_t = -\text{sign}(\tilde{M}_t) \cdot \pi_t(N) \cdot \min\left(c \cdot (|\tilde{M}_t| - U_\alpha), w_{\max}\right)$$

with $c$ a sizing constant calibrated to a target dollar risk per trade (e.g., $c$ chosen so that $|\tilde{M}_t| - U_\alpha = 1$ produces a position with 1-minute Value-at-Risk of $\$25k$). Cap $w_{\max}$ enforces a maximum position size (e.g., $\$5M$ notional).

### 10.3 Hedge construction

Hedge fast-factor exposure at the **pass-through-adjusted** loadings:
$$\mathbf{h}_t = -\delta_t \cdot \boldsymbol{\beta}_t \cdot w_t$$

In dollar terms, this gives fast-factor notional hedges of $w_t \cdot \delta_t \cdot \beta_{t,j} \cdot P_{HYG,t} / P_{F_j,t}$ for each hedgeable factor $j$.

Crucially, this hedges only the portion of HYG's expected price response that actually flows through to HYG quotes within the trade horizon. Hedging at full $\boldsymbol{\beta}_t$ over-hedges and converts a basis trade into an unintended directional bet on fast-factor mean reversion.

### 10.4 Execution

- HYG executed via passive limit orders at the inside, with a 200 ms fallback to marketable IOC if not filled.
- ES1, ZN1 hedges executed via aggressive IOC at the inside, with split-order logic for sizes exceeding 50% of top-of-book.
- All orders tagged with model version, signal value at decision time, and target position; tags persist to TCA.

