## 12. Production Considerations

### 12.1 Refit cadence

- **Daily** (overnight, 18:00 ET): full EM refit on the trailing 4-week tick history. Compares new parameters against current production parameters; flags any change exceeding 3 std-dev of the parameter's bootstrap distribution.
- **Weekly** (Sunday): regime-parameter refit including the transition logit re-estimation.
- **Monthly**: review the factor set — has any factor become weakly identified? Is there a candidate to add?
- **Ad hoc**: trigger an out-of-cycle refit if any of the daily diagnostics fails (innovation ACF, conformal coverage, parameter stability).

### 12.2 Monitoring

Real-time dashboards must show:
- Current $z_t, M_t, R_t$
- Current $\pi_t(N), \pi_t(S)$
- Current $\boldsymbol{\beta}_t, \alpha_t$ vs. their EM-refitted values (drift indicators)
- Realised vs. theoretical P&L over the trading day
- Innovation z-score and rolling Ljung–Box p-value
- Time since last HYG tick, last fast-factor tick (data feed health)

Alarms fire on:
- Standardised innovation $|\nu_t / \sqrt{F_t}| > 5$ (model surprise)
- Innovation ACF $|\rho_1| > 0.3$ (specification break)
- Regime probability flipping more than 4 times per minute (regime instability)
- Position breaching size limits
- Conformal coverage drifting outside $[\alpha - 0.05, \alpha + 0.05]$ over the trailing 4 hours

### 12.3 Failsafes

- **Kill switch on innovation ACF anomaly.** If rolling 30-minute Ljung–Box rejects whiteness at 0.1%, halt new entries (allow exits).
- **Kill switch on data feed staleness.** If any required feed is silent for more than 30 seconds during regular hours, halt new entries.
- **Position limit pre-check.** Every order re-checked against firm-wide HYG inventory limits, factor exposure limits, and overnight risk limits before submission.
- **Periodic full state checkpoint.** Every 60 seconds, persist $(\boldsymbol{\theta}_t, \mathbf{P}_t, \boldsymbol{\pi}_t, w_t)$ to disk for warm-restart capability.

### 12.4 Audit trail

Every signal-driven order carries:
- Model version (git SHA of estimation code, hash of parameter set)
- Triggering values: $\tilde{M}_t, \pi_t(N), \pi_t(S), z_t, \mathbf{F}_t$
- Timestamp at decision and at order submission
- Computed expected edge and risk

The audit trail is the primary input to TCA, model attribution, and post-mortem reviews.

