## 13. Open Items and Future Extensions

- **Replace MOVE with a swaption-implied-vol surface input.** MOVE is itself a constructed index; using the underlying 1m × 10y ATM straddle implied vol would be cleaner, at the cost of needing OTC data.
- **Replace the partial CI residual model with a non-Gaussian spec.** The residual $\xi_t^M$ has fat tails; a Student-t or NIG innovation distribution with EM extension would tighten the conformal interval in normal regime.
- **Add a co-jump filter.** Joint jumps in ES1 and ZN1 are observed and their HYG-pass-through is structurally different from continuous co-movement. Aït-Sahalia–Jacod jump tests applied at sub-second frequency would let us condition $\delta$ on jump-vs-continuous regime as a third dimension to the regime layer.
- **Cross-ETF expansion.** HYG, JNK, SHYG, USHY for HY; LQD, IGSB, IGLB for IG. Multi-asset measurement vector allows joint estimation of credit-curve fast-factor loadings.
- **Bond-side Layer.** Use TRACE prints on constituent bonds as a delayed but unbiased signal of "true" basket value. Forms a third measurement layer below NAV, potentially feeding into $R_t$ as an exogenous estimate of the non-tradable drift.

